<content class="appendix"><figure id="fs-idm379479808">
<media id="fs-idp64991424" alt="The Periodic Table of Elements, showing all 118 elements arranged in 18 groups and 7 periods. Per a provided key, metals are shaded yellow, metalloids purple, and nonmetals peach. Element symbols are printed in black for solids, blue for liquids, and red for gases at room temperature. An inset shows the layout of an individual element box, with atomic number at top left, symbol in the center, atomic mass below, and element name at the bottom. The lanthanide series (elements 57–71) and actinide series (elements 89–103) are displayed in separate rows below the main table.">
<image mime-type="image/jpeg" src="../../media/CNX_Chem_00_AA_PeriodicPU_img.jpg"/>
</media></figure>
<para id="para-00001">For a selection of accessible Period Tables, visit the <link url="https://openstax.org/l/AccessTable">Perkins School for the Blind website</link>.</para>
